    "instruction": "Using metric.csv and the stored 'metric_agg_all' kernel variable, filter metric.csv to rows where cmdb_id is in the allowed root-cause list [apache01, apache02, Tomcat01, Tomcat02, Tomcat03, Tomcat04, MG01, MG02, IG01, IG02, Mysql01, Mysql02, Redis01, Redis02] AND timestamp between 1615532400 and 1615534200 inclusive. Join each row with metric_agg_all on (cmdb_id, kpi_name) to obtain p95 and p5. Mark a row as an anomaly if value >= p95 OR value <= p5. For each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) within the window, compute: total_points_in_window, anomaly_count, earliest_anomaly_timestamp (min), latest_anomaly_timestamp (max), max_value_in_window, min_value_in_window, p95, p5. Store the full anomalies table in a kernel variable named 'metric_window_anoms'. Return a compact table of the top 20 (cmdb_id, kpi_name) pairs sorted by anomaly_count descending with the columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, total_points_in_window, anomaly_count, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, latest_anomaly_timestamp, max_value_in_window, min_value_in_window, p95, p5. Limit output to these top 20 rows only."
