{
    "analysis": "Executor found that many metric series were flagged as anomalous because global p95/p5 thresholds equal the observed values (constant or near-constant series), causing every point in the incident window to meet the anomaly condition. This makes the initial anomaly list noisy and not actionable. To find genuine faults we should focus on metric series that actually change during the window (non-constant) so we can spot significant deviations (range > 0) and then prioritize those with the largest change. This will produce a smaller, meaningful candidate set for further trace and log analysis.",
