    "instruction": "From the kernel variable 'metric_window_anoms' (row-level window-joined metric data with anomaly flags), aggregate per (cmdb_id, kpi_name) to compute: total_points_in_window, anomaly_count, min_value_in_window, max_value_in_window, value_range = max-min, earliest_anomaly_timestamp (min), latest_anomaly_timestamp (max), p95, p5. Store the full aggregated table as 'metric_candidate_ranges' in the kernel. Return a compact table of the top 20 rows sorted by value_range descending with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, total_points_in_window, anomaly_count, min_value_in_window, max_value_in_window, value_range, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, latest_anomaly_timestamp, p95, p5. Limit output to these top 20 rows only."
