    "analysis": "We retrieved earliest trace-level anomalies and found the largest early severity at timestamp 1615532460 for Tomcat01 (trace.from_root.duration_mean with severity_ratio ≈ 1.656). Other notable early high-severity items include MG02 at 1615532460 (severity ≈ 1.315) and MG01 items at 1615532400–1615532520 (modest severity). Tomcat03 shows strong aggregated trace anomalies but the sampled early rows were not anomalous; its aggregated anomalies occur later. According to the localization rules, we should (1) focus on the earliest significant anomaly that is also supported by metrics/logs, and (2) prioritize the most downstream faulty service when multiple service-level faults exist. The largest early breach we observed is Tomcat01 at 1615532460, so we must verify whether Tomcat01 exhibits concurrent metric anomalies (CPU, memory, JVM, GC, request spikes, error logs) at or just before 1615532460 to confirm it as the root cause. If Tomcat01 metrics show resource issues at that time, we can localize the root cause to Tomcat01 and derive the reason (e.g., high JVM memory, GC, CPU, or request overload).",
